                    <occupation type="literary">A native of Abyssinia, who, from fear of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName>, fled the country. 
                        He became a merchant and was engaged as an interpreter to the British Force sent into Abyssinia in <date when="1867"/>.
                        as well as to the mission of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10176Wylde">Wylde</persName> in <date when="1883"/>.</occupation>
